-- Driver Metrics
('e1e1f1a1-0002-4002-a002-000000000021', 'cd6d847c-0f2e-4ccc-bf1a-c96b08c97d4e', 'kpi',
'Driver Earnings Per Hour',
'Measures average driver earnings per active hour on the platform, critical metric for driver satisfaction and retention. Formula: (Total driver payouts + tips) / Total active hours. Active hours defined as time from first ride acceptance to last ride completion in a session. Target: $25/hour minimum across all markets to remain competitive. Current performance: $22.50/hour overall, varies by market ($18 in small cities to $28 in major metros). Tracking frequency: Real-time dashboard, weekly trending, monthly market comparison. Below $20/hour triggers driver incentive programs and demand generation campaigns.',
'ACTIVE', 1,
'{"current_value": 22.50, "target_value": 25.00, "unit": "$/hour", "formula": "(Total Payouts + Tips) / Active Hours", "tracking_frequency": "Real-time", "data_source": "Payments DB, Driver Sessions", "thresholds": {"red": "<$20", "yellow": "$20-$23", "green": ">$23"}, "trend": "increasing", "owner": "VP Operations", "related_objectives": ["Reduce Driver Churn to Below 12%"]}'::jsonb,
ARRAY['kpi', 'driver', 'earnings', 'operations', 'financial'],
NOW(), NOW()),

('e1e1f1a1-0002-4002-a002-000000000022', 'cd6d847c-0f2e-4ccc-bf1a-c96b08c97d4e', 'kpi',
'Driver Utilization Rate',
'Percentage of time drivers are actively transporting riders versus total time online. Formula: (Time on trip / Time online) × 100. Higher utilization = better driver earnings and platform efficiency. Target: 55% utilization (industry best-in-class 60%, average 45%). Current: 48%. Key drivers: match efficiency, demand density, driver positioning. Tracking: Real-time by market/time/driver segment. Improvement strategies: predictive positioning, hotspot recommendations, reduced wait times between rides. Critical for driver satisfaction (directly impacts $/hour) and operational efficiency.',
'ACTIVE', 1,
'{"current_value": 48.0, "target_value": 55.0, "unit": "%", "formula": "(Time on Trip / Time Online) × 100", "tracking_frequency": "Real-time", "data_source": "Driver Activity Logs", "thresholds": {"red": "<40%", "yellow": "40-50%", "green": ">50%"}, "trend": "increasing", "owner": "VP Operations", "benchmarks": {"industry_average": 45, "best_in_class": 60}}'::jsonb,
ARRAY['kpi', 'driver', 'utilization', 'efficiency', 'operations'],
NOW(), NOW()),

('e1e1f1a1-0002-4002-a002-000000000023', 'cd6d847c-0f2e-4ccc-bf1a-c96b08c97d4e', 'kpi',
'Driver Monthly Active Retention',
'Percentage of active drivers in month M who remain active in month M+1. Formula: (Active drivers in both M and M+1) / (Active drivers in M) × 100. Active defined as completing ≥4 rides per month. Target: 88% monthly retention. Current: 82%. Primary churn reasons: insufficient earnings (40%), flexibility of gig economy (25%), vehicle issues (15%), platform issues (10%), other (10%). High-value driver segment (>40 rides/month) retention: 94%. Tracking: Monthly cohort analysis. Retention improvements: earnings guarantees, rewards programs, vehicle maintenance support.',
'ACTIVE', 1,
'{"current_value": 82.0, "target_value": 88.0, "unit": "%", "formula": "(Drivers Active in M and M+1) / (Drivers Active in M) × 100", "tracking_frequency": "Monthly", "data_source": "Driver Activity DB", "thresholds": {"red": "<75%", "yellow": "75-85%", "green": ">85%"}, "segment_performance": {"high_value": 94, "medium_value": 84, "low_value": 65}, "owner": "VP Driver Experience"}'::jsonb,
ARRAY['kpi', 'driver', 'retention', 'churn', 'operations'],
NOW(), NOW()),

('e1e1f1a1-0002-4002-a002-000000000024', 'cd6d847c-0f2e-4ccc-bf1a-c96b08c97d4e', 'kpi',
'Driver Acceptance Rate',
'Percentage of ride requests accepted by drivers. Formula: (Accepted requests / Total requests sent to drivers) × 100. Target: 90% acceptance (indicates sufficient driver supply, attractive ride economics). Current: 85%. Low acceptance causes: unprofitable rides (long pickup distance, low fare), undesirable destinations, driver availability misclassification. Tracking: Real-time, segmented by driver tier, time of day, location. Impacts rider wait time and match efficiency. Minimum 80% to maintain service levels. Premium driver segment: 95% acceptance.',
'ACTIVE', 2,
'{"current_value": 85.0, "target_value": 90.0, "unit": "%", "formula": "(Accepted Requests / Total Sent Requests) × 100", "tracking_frequency": "Real-time", "data_source": "Matching System", "thresholds": {"red": "<80%", "yellow": "80-88%", "green": ">88%"}, "decline_reasons": {"long_pickup": 35, "low_fare": 30, "bad_destination": 20, "other": 15}, "owner": "VP Operations"}'::jsonb,
ARRAY['kpi', 'driver', 'acceptance', 'matching', 'supply'],
NOW(), NOW()),

('e1e1f1a1-0002-4002-a002-000000000025', 'cd6d847c-0f2e-4ccc-bf1a-c96b08c97d4e', 'kpi',
'Driver Cancellation Rate',
'Percentage of accepted rides that drivers cancel before pickup. Formula: (Driver cancellations / Accepted rides) × 100. Target: <2% cancellation. Current: 3.2%. Cancellation reasons: rider location issues (30%), better ride opportunity (25%), traffic/routing (20%), rider communication issues (15%), other (10%). High cancellation rates harm rider experience and increase costs. Driver penalties: <95% completion rate = temporary deactivation. Premium drivers: <1% cancellation. Tracking: Real-time with automatic penalties.',
'ACTIVE', 1,
'{"current_value": 3.2, "target_value": 2.0, "unit": "%", "formula": "(Driver Cancellations / Accepted Rides) × 100", "tracking_frequency": "Real-time", "data_source": "Ride Records", "thresholds": {"red": ">5%", "yellow": "2-5%", "green": "<2%"}, "cancellation_reasons": {"location_issues": 30, "better_ride": 25, "traffic": 20, "communication": 15, "other": 10}, "owner": "VP Operations", "penalties": "Completion rate <95% = deactivation"}'::jsonb,
ARRAY['kpi', 'driver', 'cancellation', 'reliability', 'quality'],
NOW(), NOW()),

('e1e1f1a1-0002-4002-a002-000000000026', 'cd6d847c-0f2e-4ccc-bf1a-c96b08c97d4e', 'kpi',
'Driver Rating Average',
'Average star rating (1-5 scale) given to drivers by riders. Formula: Sum(all driver ratings) / Count(ratings). Target: ≥4.85 platform average. Current: 4.82. Drivers below 4.6 receive coaching; below 4.4 for 30 days = deactivation. Rating distribution: 5-star (70%), 4-star (20%), 3-star (7%), <3-star (3%). Premium tier drivers average 4.92. Tracking: Real-time per driver, aggregated daily. Key drivers of rating: vehicle cleanliness, driving safety, route efficiency, friendliness. Rating included in match priority algorithm.',
'ACTIVE', 1,
'{"current_value": 4.82, "target_value": 4.85, "unit": "stars (1-5)", "formula": "AVG(all driver ratings)", "tracking_frequency": "Real-time", "data_source": "Rating System", "thresholds": {"red": "<4.6", "yellow": "4.6-4.8", "green": ">4.8"}, "distribution": {"5_star": 70, "4_star": 20, "3_star": 7, "below_3": 3}, "premium_tier": 4.92, "owner": "VP Quality"}'::jsonb,
ARRAY['kpi', 'driver', 'quality', 'rating', 'satisfaction'],
NOW(), NOW()),

-- Rider Metrics
('e1e1f1a1-0002-4002-a002-000000000027', 'cd6d847c-0f2e-4ccc-bf1a-c96b08c97d4e', 'kpi',
'Rider Acquisition Cost (CAC)',
'Average cost to acquire one new rider. Formula: Total marketing & sales expenses / New riders acquired. Target: $25 CAC. Current: $42. Includes paid advertising, referral incentives, partnerships, promotions. CAC varies by channel: organic ($8), referrals ($15), paid social ($38), paid search ($52), outdoor/TV ($75). Tracking: Weekly by channel. LTV:CAC ratio target 6:1 (current 4.3:1). Optimization focus: increase organic and referral percentages. High-value rider CAC acceptable up to $60 if predicted LTV >$400.',
'ACTIVE', 1,
'{"current_value": 42.0, "target_value": 25.0, "unit": "$", "formula": "Marketing Expenses / New Riders", "tracking_frequency": "Weekly", "data_source": "Marketing Analytics", "thresholds": {"red": ">$50", "yellow": "$35-$50", "green": "<$35"}, "by_channel": {"organic": 8, "referral": 15, "paid_social": 38, "paid_search": 52, "traditional": 75}, "ltv_cac_ratio": 4.3, "target_ratio": 6.0, "owner": "CMO"}'::jsonb,
ARRAY['kpi', 'marketing', 'acquisition', 'financial', 'rider'],
NOW(), NOW()),

('e1e1f1a1-0002-4002-a002-000000000028', 'cd6d847c-0f2e-4ccc-bf1a-c96b08c97d4e', 'kpi',
'Rider Retention Rate (30-Day)',
'Percentage of riders who take another ride within 30 days of their first ride. Formula: (Riders with 2+ rides in 30 days / New riders) × 100. Target: 40% 30-day retention. Current: 32%. Retention critical for positive unit economics (CAC payback requires 4+ rides). Retention drivers: ride quality (4.5+ rating = 55% retention), pricing satisfaction, pickup speed, first-ride experience. Cohort analysis by acquisition channel shows referrals highest retention (48%) vs paid ads (28%). Tracking: Daily cohort monitoring.',
'ACTIVE', 1,
'{"current_value": 32.0, "target_value": 40.0, "unit": "%", "formula": "(Riders with 2+ rides in 30d / New Riders) × 100", "tracking_frequency": "Daily", "data_source": "Ride Analytics", "thresholds": {"red": "<25%", "yellow": "25-35%", "green": ">35%"}, "by_channel": {"referral": 48, "organic": 42, "paid_social": 30, "paid_search": 28}, "drivers": "Ride quality, pricing, speed", "owner": "VP Growth"}'::jsonb,
ARRAY['kpi', 'rider', 'retention', 'growth', 'engagement'],
NOW(), NOW()),

('e1e1f1a1-0002-4002-a002-000000000029', 'cd6d847c-0f2e-4ccc-bf1a-c96b08c97d4e', 'kpi',
'Rider Lifetime Value (LTV)',
'Predicted total net revenue from a rider over their lifetime. Formula: (Average revenue per ride × Rides per year × Average customer lifespan) - CAC. Target: $250 LTV. Current: $180. Components: rides per year (avg 28, target 40), revenue per ride ($18.50), lifespan (2.3 years, target 3.5 years), retention rate (60% year-over-year). High-value segment (business travelers): $520 LTV. Tracking: Quarterly cohort analysis with predictive models. LTV improvement strategies: loyalty program, subscription, ride frequency campaigns.',
'ACTIVE', 1,
'{"current_value": 180.0, "target_value": 250.0, "unit": "$", "formula": "(Revenue/Ride × Rides/Year × Lifespan) - CAC", "tracking_frequency": "Quarterly", "data_source": "Financial Analytics", "components": {"rides_per_year": 28, "revenue_per_ride": 18.50, "lifespan_years": 2.3, "retention_rate": 60}, "segments": {"high_value": 520, "medium_value": 180, "low_value": 85}, "owner": "CFO"}'::jsonb,
ARRAY['kpi', 'rider', 'ltv', 'financial', 'value'],
NOW(), NOW()),

('e1e1f1a1-0002-4002-a002-000000000030', 'cd6d847c-0f2e-4ccc-bf1a-c96b08c97d4e', 'kpi',
'Rider Cancellation Rate',
'Percentage of requested rides cancelled by riders before driver arrival. Formula: (Rider cancellations / Total ride requests) × 100. Target: <5% cancellation. Current: 7.2%. Cancellation reasons: long wait time (45%), price shock (25%), changed plans (15%), driver rating concerns (10%), other (5%). Cancellations after driver dispatched incur $5 fee (after 2 min grace period). High cancellation rates indicate poor ETA estimation or pricing transparency. Tracking: Real-time with automated alerts >10%.',
